PiperOrigin-RevId: 325139525

Introduced a new py-C++ bridge that is built on top of arrow C-ABI structs. This new bridge does not assume C++ ABI compatibility, and allows us to build Arrow C++ from source and make tfx_bsl self-contained (i.e. does not rely on libarrow.so or libarrow_python.so).

The usage of the new bridge is controlled by a macro TFX_BSL_USE_ARROW_C_ABI, which is defined (see .bazelrc) by default.

tfx_bsl will not support building with pyarrow shared libraries (TFX_BSL_USE_ARROW_C_ABI undefined) any more, although it remains buildable (with some tweak in WORKSPACE needed).

This change obviates the need for configure.sh, as well as complicated bazel rules to find pyarrow installation. Instead, it fetches arrow source code from a fixed revision.

This change also allows tfx_bsl to depend on a wide range of pyarrow versions, as long as pyarrow's API used by tfx_bsl is stable. For now, we set the requirement to pyarrow>=0.17,<1.

PiperOrigin-RevId: 324255791

Changed the internal of DetectCompressionType so that:

- it's not a tf.function any more (but still it's composed of only TF ops and
  thus can be embedded in a tf.function or graph).
- it's free of stateful / control flow ops.

This change is for TF 1.x compatibility, as
tf.compat.v1.data.make_one_shot_iterator() does not support capturing
stateful / control flow ops.
